      "content": "the \"counting\" idea is good, i'll check the delta on the object count. \n\nabout the remove_oldest() part, i'm looking at the implementation now. it's a custom circular buffer, not a vector. it's supposed to just drop the head pointer and move the index. \n\ncan you walk me through the most common ways this specific kind of logic fails in C++? like what exactly would cause the memory to stay allocated even if the index moves forward? i'm trying to visualize how the pointer gets stuck.",
